<br>
I will not risk my group to run and go do a rez, but instead will ask the person to have the corpse dragged to me.  If I can be spared, I will leave the group and rez.<br>
<br>
If I cannot do the rez, I politely explain that I am unable.<br>
<br>
I have never asked for donations, but will accept them when offered.  I do greatly appreciate donations, they help cover my gem costs.<br>
<br>
I stay on roleplay simply because I want to avoid those long distance requests for rezzes from someone who does a /who cleric all.<br>
<br>
I will not ignore a request for a rez in ooc or shout unless I am unable to rez.<br>
<br>
I have made many friends by just rezzing them.  I am a firm believer of what comes around goes around.  So far, it hasn't failed me yet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
